<LegalLayout
  title="Platform & Candidate-Data Privacy Notice — Aramo"
  description="How the Aramo platform handles candidate and client data: our controller/processor roles, the data we handle and why, consent-gated portability, assessments with reasons (never a score), retention, security, and your rights."
  heading="Platform & Candidate-Data Privacy Notice"
>
  <h2>Who we are and our role</h2>
  <p>
    The Aramo platform is operated by Astre Consulting Services Inc. Our role
    depends on how data reaches us:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      When a staffing firm uses Aramo to run its hiring, that firm decides how
      candidate data is used. The firm is the <strong>data controller</strong>,
      and Aramo acts as its <strong>processor</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
      When a candidate provides information directly to the platform under their
      own consent — for verification or portable credentials — Aramo is the
      <strong>controller</strong> of that relationship.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What data the platform handles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identification and contact details.</strong></li>
    <li>
      <strong>Professional history and work product</strong> — roles,
      submittals, resumes, and related records.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Verification and evidence artifacts</strong> — the records that
      stand behind an assessment.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Consent and preference records.</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why we handle it</h2>
  <p>
    To operate the staffing firm’s hiring workflow, to resolve and verify
    identity, and to produce evidence-graded assessments.
  </p>

  <h2>Consent and portability</h2>
  <p>
    This is the part that makes Aramo different. Signals about a candidate
    activate across firms <strong>only with that candidate’s consent</strong>.
    Verification a candidate has earned is portable only where the candidate
    chooses to carry it. When a candidate consents to share, that consent is
    specific to the destination, written in plain language, and can be withdrawn
    up to the moment of transfer.
  </p>

  <h2>Assessments, not scores</h2>
  <p>
    Aramo assesses evidence across dimensions and shows the reasons behind each
    result. People are <strong>never</strong> given a numeric score, a grade, or
    a rank. Automated processing proposes; a person decides every submittal and
    hiring action.
  </p>

  <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
  <p>
    We keep platform data under the staffing firm’s direction and applicable law,
    and we honor candidate rights — including deletion requests — as the law
    provides.
  </p>

  <h2>Security commitments</h2>
  <p>
    Tenant isolation so one firm’s data never feeds another’s, encryption in
    transit, and least-privilege access. We describe our commitments here without
    disclosing internal architecture.
  </p>

  <h2>Subprocessors</h2>
  <p>
    We use a short, vetted list of vendors to run the platform. See our current
    <a href="/legal/subprocessors">Subprocessor List</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights and how to exercise them</h2>
  <p>
    Where your staffing firm is the controller, exercise your rights through that
    firm — we help them respond. Where Aramo is the controller (data you gave us
    directly), write to <a href="mailto:hello@aramo.ai">hello@aramo.ai</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>We update this page and the version line below when this notice changes.</p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>This notice is governed by the laws of [STATE — counsel].</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about platform data? Write to <a href="mailto:hello@aramo.ai"
      >hello@aramo.ai</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
